# 🔐 Cloud-Native Secrets Management with CyberArk Conjur, Terraform & AWS

A production-inspired demonstration of centralized secrets management using **CyberArk Conjur OSS**, **Terraform**, **AWS**, **Docker**, and **Python**.

This project provisions cloud infrastructure using Terraform, deploys a CyberArk Conjur environment, and demonstrates how an application can securely retrieve secrets at runtime through the Conjur REST API using a **least-privilege application identity**, eliminating the need for hardcoded credentials.

---

## Acknowledgements

The Docker-based Conjur environment is based on the official CyberArk Conjur OSS Quickstart and has been adapted for this project. The infrastructure provisioning, application integration, policy design, and end-to-end secrets management workflow were implemented as part of this project.

---


## 📌 Problem Statement

Hardcoding credentials in application source code, configuration files, or environment variables introduces significant security risks:

- Credentials can be accidentally committed to source control.
- Password rotation requires application configuration changes.
- Every application must manage secrets independently.
- Overprivileged service accounts increase the attack surface.

This project demonstrates how centralized secrets management solves these problems by allowing applications to authenticate to CyberArk Conjur and retrieve secrets dynamically at runtime.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
                     AWS Cloud

        ┌─────────────────────────────┐
        │ Terraform Infrastructure    │
        └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                       │
                Provision Resources
                       │
                       ▼
               EC2 Instance (Python App)
                       │
                       │ HTTPS
                       ▼
        ┌─────────────────────────────┐
        │ CyberArk Conjur OSS         │
        │ (Docker Environment)        │
        └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                       │
                Authenticate Host
                       │
                Short-lived Token
                       │
                       ▼
              Retrieve Database Secrets
```

